<p>Some of this history was told to Brenda Bowers by Bob Muchamore, who was General Coordinator of the project from 2001. Part of this history has been gleaned from the historic snapshots of the FreeCEN website which are preserved by the <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230505101052/https://www.freecen.org.uk/" title="https://web.archive.org/web/20230505101052/https://www.freecen.org.uk/">Internet Archive </a>on its ‘Wayback’ machine, including those from the earliest days when <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20020718110511/http://freecen.rootsweb.org/" title="https://web.archive.org/web/20020718110511/http://freecen.rootsweb.org/">FreeCEN did not have its own website</a>.</p>
<p>FreeCEN started in 1999 and had125 volunteers by December, 2000.</p>
