<p>FreeCEN</p>
<p>Brenda joined the project as Coordinator for Nottinghamshire about 1 month after Bob retired as the project Chair, and served as Chair until 2021.</p>One of the main instigators was Brian Randell (GenUKI, Devon and Newcastle University), with considerable (and on-going) support from Bob Muchamore (AUS).  The 1891 Devon transcription was instigated as the pilot project, followed in mid-2000 by the 1891 Cornwall transcription. By the end of 2000, four other counties had been initiated, and more ensued. Bob took over General Co-ordination of the Project in August, 2001. Considerable aid to the Project was also given by the late Roy Conibear (CAN).  <br /><p>Brenda  then took on the role of helping anyone with queries working alongside Bob Muchamore. With the introduction of Microsoft XP and Bob only having Windows 32 he had difficulty helping them so they shared the issues.</p>After the death of Bob Muchamore in 2004, Brenda was the Assistant Chair  to Dave Newbury when he took over as Chairman.  When Dave became seriously ill, in 2008, Brenda took over as Chair temporarily, but sadly Dave passed away two years later.<br />NEXT SLIDE The organization in the first decade or so included separate Heads for Scotland and Wales, reflecting the differences in censuses in those countries.<br />Although started as an independent project, FreeCEN always worked closely with FreeBMD, and it was a natural move to become a project of FreeBMD the charity.  FreeBMD the charity was then renamed to be Free UK Genealogy, reflecting that it did far more than FreeBMD the project.<br />But more about details of the  work….</div>
